    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>4 cups dashi (Japanese soup stock)</li>
            <li>3 tablespoons miso paste</li>
            <li>1 block (about 8 oz) tofu, cubed</li>
            <li>2 green onions, finely sliced</li>
            <li>1 sheet nori (seaweed), cut into thin strips (optional)</li>
            <li>1 cup mushrooms, sliced (shiitake or enoki mushrooms work well)</li>
            <li>1 cup spinach, washed and trimmed</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Miso Soup</li>
            <li>Japanese</li>
            <li>Soup</li>
            <li>Tofu</li>
            <li>Vegetarian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a pot, bring the dashi to a simmer over medium heat.</li>
            <li>In a small bowl, dilute the miso paste with a small amount of dashi to create a smooth mixture.</li>
            <li>Gradually add the miso mixture to the pot, stirring well to combine. Be careful not to boil the soup once the miso is added.</li>
            <li>Add tofu, mushrooms, and green onions to the soup. Simmer for about 5 minutes until the tofu is heated through.</li>
            <li>Add spinach to the pot and cook until it wilts (about 1-2 minutes).</li>
            <li>Remove the pot from heat. Ladle the miso soup into bowls.</li>
            <li>Garnish with nori strips if desired.</li>
            <li>Serve the hot and comforting Miso Soup immediately.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your homemade Miso Soup!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

